# Identifiers exempt from the .bni naming-convention check.
# One `<path>:<identifier>` entry per line, relative to the examples repo root.
# Comments start with #.

# Private (lowercase) generic helpers. A generic function's body must live in the
# .bni so a consumer can monomorphize it at the call site (template-in-header),
# and that extends to any private helper the body calls — so these are internal
# despite appearing in the .bni. They are NOT part of the package's public API.
generics/pkg/hashmap.bni:slotFor
generics/pkg/hashmap.bni:grow
